snippet: Some incumbents were defeated by fellow Democrats and some Republicans faced the possibility of the same fate under new redistricting rules.
abstract: First election since California's overhauled electoral system was adopted played havoc with some of state's Congressional delegation; some incumbents were defeated by fellow Democrats and some Republicans facing possibility of the same fate under new redistricting rules, with their races still too close to have been called.
lead_paragraph: Some incumbents were defeated by fellow Democrats and some Republicans faced the possibility of the same fate under new redistricting rules.
